Jacob Ojee’s brace in the first half ensured Shujaa sealed a comfortable 24-0 win over Zimbabwe in their Solidarity Camp opening match. The KCB winger sliced through the Zimbabwe defence to score twice as Tony converted both for a 14-0 lead heading to the interval’s. Alvin “Buffa Otieno” bulldozed the Zimbabwean defence to score in the second half for a 19-0 lead with Omondi missing the extras. Shujaa would go on to score the final unconverted try to seal their victory with a comfortable win for the Innocent Simiyu charge’s. Kenya will face South Africa 2 in their second game of the day as they seek to finish the day on a high note awaiting tomorrow’s quarter finals seeding. Also Read: Video Of The Day: Guns galore